You can skip a single test function by using the `@pytest.mark.skip` decorator, which may be passed an optional reason.

    @pytest.mark.skip(reason="no way of currently testing this")
    def test_the_unknown(): ...

Alternatively, you can use the `pytest.skip` function without any arguments to skip the entire test function.

    def test_function():
        if not valid_config():
            pytest.skip()
